children.subject: Haha, yes it's 2021 -- thanks for catching that!
Huh I suppose this event is happening in April 2021 not last year, right?

history.content:
Hi! I hope everyone had a great spring break!! I wanted to share this opportunity for anyone who is/knows beginners in tech and are interested in learning how to build web/mobile apps. 

 

FEMTech is partnering with Cal Hacks to host the FEMTech Bootcamp, a guided hackathon dedicated to beginners and underrepresented groups in the tech field. Join us for a day of introductory workshops (including web/mobile development, design, and more), that will help you build creative projects from ground up. We are providing mentorship, cash prizes for the top projects, and credits for meals during the 12-hour Bootcamp! No experience is required!
Where: Virtual!
When: April 24th, 2021
Apply here: tinyurl.com/femtechbootcamp
Checkout our event website: tinyurl.com/femtech2021
